<body>
<p>Reports Hibernate @Find annotation errors</p>
<ul>
  <li>The return type of an annotated method must be an entity type <b>E</b>, or one of the following types:
    <ul>
      <li>java.util.List&lt;E&gt;</li>
      <li>org.hibernate.query.Query&lt;E&gt;</li>
      <li>org.hibernate.query.SelectionQuery&lt;E&gt;</li>
      <li>jakarta.persistence.Query&lt;E&gt;</li>
      <li>jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery&lt;E&gt;</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>The names and types of the parameters of a finder method must match exactly with the names and types of persistent fields of the
    entity type returned by the finder method.
  </li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>